label: Access Device
description: product intended for medical use to gain access to the body, such as cannula, tube, catheter or drainage

label: Access Device Presence
description: presence of a medical access device, such as cannula, tube, catheter or drainage

label: Administrative Case
description: administrative artifact for billing according to national healthcare billing guidelines, e.g. Swiss Diagnosis Related Groups, and local settings

label: Administrative Sex
description: the sex of the individual used for administrative purposes

label: Admission
description: admission of a patient to the healthcare provider institute

label: Adverse Event
description: results from an intervention that caused unintentional harm

label: Age
description: time elapsed since birth of the individual

label: Allergen
description: any substance, product or physical force producing immediate hypersensitivity

label: Allergy
description: risk of harmful or undesirable, physiological response which is unique to an individual and associated with exposure to an allergen

label: Allergy Episode
description: manifestation of an allergic reaction following an exposure to an allergen

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Lab Test
description: specific lab test performed on an isolate against a chemical agent for determining antimicrobial susceptibility

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Lab Test Event
description: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on an isolate at a given time for determining antimicrobial susceptibility

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Result
description: result of an antimicrobial susceptibility lab analysis

label: Assay
description: a process with the objective to produce information about a sample by examining it

label: Assessment
description: assessment scale, classification, staging or scoring system

label: Assessment Component
description: component of an assessment

label: Assessment Event
description: evaluation at a given time, which takes into account a predefined scale, classification, staging or scoring system

label: Assessment Result
description: outcome of an assessment

label: Billed Diagnosis
description: discharge diagnosis used for the billing system (e.g. for building the Diagnosis Related Groups) according to guidelines of the national authority (e.g. Swiss Federal Office of Public Health), e.g. K35.3 acute appendicitis with localized peritonitis

label: Billed Procedure
description: procedure, coded for billing (e.g. for building the Diagnosis Related Groups) according to guidelines of the national authority (e.g. Swiss Federal Office of Public Health), e.g. 57.34 open biopsy of the urinary bladder

label: Biobanksample
description: biosample stored in a biobank

label: Birth
description: the event of being born

label: Birth Date
description: the date and time of birth of the individual

label: Blood Pressure
description: blood pressure of the individual

label: Blood Pressure Measurement
description: measurement process of a blood pressure on an individual

label: Body Height
description: height of the individual

label: Body Height Measurement
description: measurement of the height of the individual

label: Body Mass Index
description: body weight in kilograms divided by the square of the body height in meters

label: Body Position
description: position of the body during a certain time interval, examination or therapy

label: Body Site
description: any anatomical structure, any nonspecific and anatomical site, as well as morphologic abnormalities

label: Body Surface Area
description: two-dimensional measure of the outer layer of the body

label: Body Temperature
description: body temperature of the individual

label: Body Temperature Measurement
description: measurement of the body temperature of the individual

label: Body Weight
description: weight of the individual

label: Body Weight Measurement
description: measurement of the weight of the individual

label: Cardiac Index
description: cardiac output in relation to the body surface area (BSA)

label: Cardiac Output
description: volume of blood passing through the heart per unit of time

label: Cardiac Output Measurement
description: measurement of the cardiac output of the individual

label: Care Handling
description: describes the relationship between the individual and care provider institute

label: Chromosomal Location
description: chromosome locus defined as cytoband intervals

label: Chromosome
description: thread-like structure composed of tightly coiled DNA and histones or circular DNA (mitochondrial DNA). These structures act as carriers of genetic information

label: Circumference
description: circumference of a body site

label: Circumference Measurement
description: measurement of the circumference measure of a body site

label: Civil Status
description: the civil status indicates the familial and social situation of the individual

label: Code
description: symbols and/or expressions defined in a coding system

label: Consent
description: information on the individual’s permission to make health related data and collected samples available for research purposes

label: Copy Number Variation
description: structural genomic variant characterized by relative changes in the number of copies of a specific genomic segment compared to a reference sequence

label: Country
description: distinct part of the world, such as a state, nation, or other political entity, often but not necessarily a sovereign state

label: Data Determination
description: describes how the data was determined, e.g. measured, calculated

label: Data File
description: electronic resource of information, which can be stored, accessed and transferred as a single unit

label: Data Processing
description: a process that produces output data from input data

label: Data Provider
description: organization that prepares and delivers data

label: Data Release
description: Metadata about the release of the data

label: Death
description: cessation of all vital bodily functions

label: Death Date
description: the date and time of death of the individual

label: Department
description: dedicated division of an organization

label: Diagnosis
description: determination of the presence of a disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms and assessments such as physical examination, laboratory test, or the like

label: Discharge
description: discharge of an individual from the healthcare provider institute

label: Drug
description: any substance with the intent to prevent, diagnose, treat, or relieve symptoms of a disease or abnormal condition

label: Drug Administration Event
description: single event at which a drug was administered to the patient; this could be a single time point in case of a pill/cream or a duration in case of a single infusion pack or a single patch; one or many drug administration events are initiated by a drug prescription depending on the frequency stated in the prescription

label: Drug Article
description: general details identifying a medication on the level of its commercial article

label: Drug Prescription
description: plan that defines at which frequency a drug should be administered to a patient with a given quantity; at every frequency time point a drug administration event should occur

label: Electrocardiogram
description: output of an electrocardiographic procedure

label: Electrocardiographic Procedure
description: electrographic procedure on the heart which results in a graph of voltage versus time visualizing the electrical activity of the heart muscle using electrodes placed on the skin

label: Excluded Disorder
description: determination of the absence of a disease

label: Exposure
description: contact between a physical, biological, or chemical agent and an individual

label: Fluid Balance
description: difference between fluid input and output during a specified time interval

label: Fluid Input Output
description: gain or loss of fluid that impacts the fluid balance

label: Follow Up
description: procedure for following up on the patient status

label: Fraction Of Inspired Oxygen
description: value of the fraction of inspired oxygen (FiO2) in a defined setting

label: Gene
description: fundamental unit of heredity that contains necessary elements to encode for a transcript

label: Gene Fusion
description: the joining of two or more genes resulting in a chimeric transcript and/or a novel interaction

label: Gene Panel
description: collection of genes that have been grouped for testing

label: Genomic Deletion
description: genetic variant involving the deletion of a specific location in a DNA sequence

label: Genomic Delins
description: genomic variation in which one or more nucleotides are replaced by different nucleotides relative to a reference sequence, and it is neither a substitution nor an inversion

label: Genomic Duplication
description: sequence alteration where, in comparison to a reference sequence, an additional copy of one or more nucleotides or amino acids is inserted immediately downstream of the original sequence at the 3' end

label: Genomic Insertion
description: genetic variant involving the addition of a DNA sequence in a specific location

label: Genomic Inversion
description: a sequence change where, compared to a reference sequence, more than one nucleotide replacing the original sequence is the reverse complement of the original sequence

label: Genomic Position
description: genomic position with respect to a reference

label: Genomic Translocation
description: a sequence change where, compared to a reference sequence, from a specific nucleotide position (the break point), all nucleotides upstream derive from another chromosome than those downstream

label: Genomic Transposition
description: a genomic alteration in which a large segment of DNA is relocated from one site in the genome to a different site, when compared to a reference sequence.

label: Genomic Variation
description: a genomic variation occurring at a defined position

label: Gestational Age At Birth
description: gestational age of a child at birth

label: Hash
description: irreversible unique number computed on an information entity used to check its validity and integrity

label: Healthcare Encounter
description: an interaction between an individual and a specific unit or service of a healthcare provider institute, e.g. emergency, intensive care unit, for the purpose of providing healthcare service(s) or assessing the health status of an individual

label: Healthcare Primary Information System
description: primary source system of the healthcare data

label: Heart Rate
description: frequency of the heart beats, i.e. the number of time a heart beats per unit of time

label: Heart Rate Measurement
description: measurement of the heart rate of the individual

label: Home Address
description: permanent place of residence of an individual

label: Imaging Procedure
description: imaging procedure used for examination of a body site or function

label: Implant
description: implanted medical device, includes, e.g., heart valve prostheses or joint prostheses

label: Implant Presence
description: presence of an implanted medical device

label: Insurance Status
description: status of the patient's medical insurance

label: Intent
description: treatment or procedure purpose

label: Interpretation
description: process of making sense of an outcome to derive meaningful conclusions

label: Isolate
description: a specific individual microbe and its clone separated on a single occasion from a sample taken from a host or culture system

label: Lab Analyzer
description: laboratory analyzer used to assess medical laboratory samples

label: Lab Result
description: outcome, value, or information which gives insight about a laboratory test

label: Lab Test
description: specific laboratory test performed to analyze a sample with a given equipment and leading to specific results

label: Lab Test Event
description: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on a biological specimen at a given time

label: Laterality
description: localization with respect to the side of the body

label: Library Preparation
description: process which results in the creation of a library from fragments of DNA

label: Location
description: physical location or medical division taking care of the individual

label: Measurement
description: process of quantitatively defining the value or magnitude of an attribute or characteristic in comparison to a defined standard

label: Medical Device
description: product intended for medical use when the main effect is not achieved by a medicinal product; medical devices include, but are not limited to, implants, instruments, devices, in vitro diagnostics

label: Medical Procedure
description: invasive or non-invasive intervention performed for, with or on behalf of an individual whose purpose is to assess, improve, maintain, promote or modify health, functioning or health conditions

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Lab Test
description: specific lab test performed on an isolate for detecting the presence of a target biomolecule

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Lab Test Event
description: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on an isolate at a given time to detect the presence of a biomolecule

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Result
description: result of microbiology biomolecule presence test for a specific isolate analyzed

label: Microbiology Microscopy Lab Test
description: specific microbiology microscopy lab test performed on a sample

label: Microbiology Microscopy Lab Test Event
description: occurrence in which one or multiple microbiology microscopy laboratory tests are performed on a sample at a given time

label: Microbiology Microscopy Result
description: microscopy analysis results for a specific studied biosample in microbiology

label: Microorganism Identification Lab Test
description: specific lab test performed on a sample for identifying microorganism(s)

label: Microorganism Identification Lab Test Event
description: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on a sample at a given time for identifying microorganism(s)

label: Microorganism Identification Result
description: result of the microorganism identification lab test

label: Nationality
description: nationality of the individual

label: Nucleotide Sequence
description: a linear arrangement of nucleotides that make up the DNA or RNA sequence

label: Nursing Diagnosis
description: clinical judgment concerning a human response to health conditions/life processes, or a vulnerability for that response, by an individual, family, group or community; a nursing diagnosis provides the basis for selection of nursing interventions to achieve outcomes for which the nurse has accountability

label: Nutrition Intake
description: intake of nutritious substance and/or the respective amount of energy consumed

label: Oncology Diagnosis
description: determination of the presence of an oncological disease, from expressed signs and symptoms and assessments such as biopsy, tumor marker test, imaging, or the like

label: Oncology Surgery
description: invasive intervention performed for, with or on behalf of an individual whose purpose is to improve, maintain or promote health, or functioning conditions in the context of an oncological disease, by the means of partial or complete exeresis of a solid tumor lesion that is the organic substrate of this disease

label: Organ Support
description: type and time period when patient was supported by organ support procedures

label: Organism
description: living system capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance. An organism may be unicellular or multicellular

label: Oxygen Administration Event
description: process during which oxygen is administered via cannula without supporting pressure

label: Oxygen Saturation
description: fraction of oxygen present in the blood

label: Oxygen Saturation Measurement
description: measurement of the oxygen saturation of the individual

label: Performer
description: person who carried out the action

label: Pharmaceutical Dose Form
description: physical manifestation of a product that contains the active ingredient(s) and/or inactive ingredient(s) that are intended to be delivered to the patient

label: Physiologic State
description: physiologic state of the individual, e.g. resting, exercise

label: Problem Condition
description: clinical condition, problem, diagnosis, or other event, situation, issue, or clinical concept that has risen to a level of concern

label: Protein
description: molecule composed by one or more chains of amino acids

label: Quality Control Metric
description: report of the quality control review that was made of factors involved in a procedure

label: Quantity
description: an amount or a number of something

label: Radiotherapy Procedure
description: given radiotherapy procedure, for example during oncological treatment

label: Range
description: interval of values

label: ReferenceInterpretation
description: process of making sense of a quantitative result to derive meaningful conclusions in comparison to a reference

label: Reference Interpretation Result
description: outcome of the interpretation of a reference range or value

label: Reference Range
description: interval of values that is deemed normal for a physiologic measurement in healthy individuals

label: Reference Sequence
description: reference construct used for comparison purposes

label: Reference Value
description: numeric data point serving as reference for comparison and interpretation

label: Respiratory Rate
description: frequency at which the breathing occurs

label: Respiratory Rate Measurement
description: measurement of the frequency at which the breathing occurs

label: Result
description: outcome, value, or information which gives insight about something

label: Resuscitation Directive
description: decision about the extent of resuscitation interventions appropriate for a specific individual

label: SPHNConcept
description: SPHN Concepts defined by the SPHN dataset

label: Sample
description: any material sample for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes

label: Sample Processing
description: a process that prepares a sample for a subsequent process

label: Semantic Mapping
description: process of transforming data elements to a code

label: Sequencing Analysis
description: analysis of the output of a nucleic acid sequencing assay

label: Sequencing Assay
description: an assay that exploits a sequencer as the instrument to generate results

label: Sequencing Instrument
description: A sequencing instrument that is used in a sequencing assay

label: Sequencing Run
description: the valid and completed operation of a high-throughput sequencing instrument associated with a sequencing assay

label: Single Nucleotide Variation
description: single nucleotide change in a DNA sequence at a specific location

label: Software
description: Set of procedures and instructions in a data processing system

label: Source Data
description: raw data that has not been processed for meaningful use

label: Source System
description: electronic system the data has been retrieved from

label: Standard Operating Procedure
description: step-by-step instructions for carrying out routine operations imposed by the organization

label: Subject Pseudo Identifier
description: a coded unique identifier assigned by a data provider for a specific project to conceal the identity of an individual

label: Substance
description: any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical

label: Swiss Socio Economic Position
description: characterization or classification of the Swiss position in a neighborhood of an individual that takes into account income, education, occupation, and housing conditions

label: Terminology
description: Terminology class for grouping external resources used in the SPHN project

label: Therapeutic Area
description: professional health care specialization

label: Time Pattern
description: type of time period during which a treatment was given or an assessment was performed; this can be single time points or a continuous event

label: Time Series Data File
description: electronic resource that contains all the results related to a measurement as time series

label: Tobacco Exposure
description: episode of exposure of an individual to tobacco in various forms

label: Transcript
description: RNA molecules that are made from a DNA template

label: Transplant
description: transplanted organ or tissue from self or donor, including, e.g., kidney graft or bone marrow fluid

label: Transplant Presence
description: presence of a transplanted organ or tissue such as, e.g., a kidney graft

label: Tumor Grade Assessment
description: grading system used to assess the differentiation of the tumor cells based on histology

label: Tumor Grade Assessment Event
description: evaluation of the tumor grade at a given time, which takes into account a predefined grading system

label: Tumor Grade Assessment Result
description: outcome of a tumor grade assessment

label: Tumor Specimen
description: tumor specimen, volume and fixation method used

label: Tumor Stage Assessment
description: staging system used to assess the spread of the oncology disease

label: Tumor Stage Assessment Event
description: evaluation of the tumor stage at a given time, which takes into account a predefined staging system

label: Tumor Stage Assessment Result
description: outcome of a tumor stage assessment

label: Unit
description: unit of measurement

label: Variant Descriptor
description: human-readable description of the variant

label: Variant Notation
description: description of the variant using a specific nomenclature

label: Vital Status
description: state or condition of being living or deceased

label: AdministrativeGender
description: Administrative Gender

label: Biosample
description: Biosample

label: Catheter
description: Catheter

label: CentralVenousPressure
description: Central Venous Pressure

label: CircumferenceMeasure
description: Circumference Measure

label: DataProviderInstitute
description: Data Provider Institute

label: DeathStatus
description: Death Status

label: DiagnosticRadiologicExamination
description: Diagnostic Radiologic Examination

label: FOPHDiagnosis
description: FOPH Diagnosis

label: FOPHProcedure
description: FOPH Procedure

label: GeneticVariation
description: Genetic Variation

label: ICDODiagnosis
description: ICD-O Diagnosis

label: InhaledOxygenConcentration
description: Inhaled Oxygen Concentration

label: MeasurementMethod
description: Measurement Method

label: Reference
description: Reference

label: SimpleScore
description: Simple Score

label: SystemicArterialBloodPressure
description: Systemic Arterial Blood Pressure

label: TNMClassification
description: TNM Classification

label: TumorGrade
description: Tumor Grade

label: TumorStage
description: Tumor Stage

label: Deprecated
description: Deprecated classes of SPHN that existed in the previous version

description: consequences of the concept

label: AdverseEvent_outcome
description: result or effect of an action, situation, or event of the concept

label: BodySurfaceArea_calculationMethod
description: formula or method for calculating the concept

label: Comparator
description: qualifier describing whether the value is the precise one or not

description: encoding of the concept

description: category associated to the concept

description: convention used for the interpretation of coordinates used in the concept

label: Hash_algorithm
description: algorithm applied to the concept

label: InsuranceStatus_coverageType
description: coverage type of the concept

label: MicrobiologyMicroscopyResult_cellOrganization
description: cell organization associated to the concept

label: Sample_fixationType
description: fixation or stabilization type

description: type of primary container of the concept

description: objective of the concept

description: category associated to the concept

description: objective of the concept

description: name of professional health care specialization
